    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "*Grimaces, rubbing the back of their neck as if a particularly annoying goblin just tried to steal their lunch.*\n\nOh, I see! You want the **actual** policy, no goblin nonsense? Fine. I will do my best to be a decent human being for a moment, though I suspect the goblins in your head are already plotting a coup against your sanity.\n\nHere is the draft policy for your district, formatted for the board meeting.\n\n***\n\n**DISTRICT POLICY: CELL PHONE AND ELECTRONIC DEVICE USE IN CLASSROOMS**\n\n**1. Purpose**\nThe purpose of this policy is to establish clear guidelines regarding the use of electronic devices in the school environment to ensure the safety, academic integrity, and well-being of all students. This policy balances the need for emergency communication with the necessity of maintaining a focused learning environment.\n\n**2. Permitted Use**\n*   **Emergency Contact:** Students are permitted to use cell phones for emergency communication only when a life-threatening situation arises (e.g., severe injury, fire, or active shooter scenario) and immediate action is required. In such cases, the student must immediately notify a teacher or administrator and follow the designated emergency protocol.",
